					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-8975850#post-4067832</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-8975850/the-hitchhiker-s-guide-to-the-library#post-4067832</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 26 Nov 2018 01:50:30 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>mayoculpa</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3489662</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I am very sorry everyone. I woke up with this in my head this morning and I decided to let it corrupt me utterly.</p> <p>&#8230;I especially apologize to the tag team.</p> <p>I intend this to be a Project Crossover post, but I couldn't find a procedure to follow so I don't know if it's copacetic. This links to several SCPs, namely <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-4949">SCP-4949 (Wondertainment / dado play doctor kit)</a>, <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-3778">SCP-3778 (Possums)</a>, <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-3765">SCP-3765 (Beavers)</a>, <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-2050">SCP-2050 (Squirrels)</a> and <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/scp-3011">SCP-3011 (Skinks)</a>.</p> <p>It was inspired by a throwaway comment in LordStonefish's <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/asmr-by-dado">asmr by dado</a> video. My ears heard &quot;for-profit church,&quot; but the haemster in my heart heard &quot;FOUR-PROPHET church&quot; and the seed of a terrible idea took root.</p> <p>Kakroom helped me crit this and make a few plot points clearer, and rounderhouse gave it a quick look-over, though really, they are fine people and should not be blamed.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
